ZCZC DE75
FAROE ISLANDS
072248UTC DES 13
FAROESE WEATHER BULLETIN FM DMI ISSUED AT 2225 UTC (WIND FORCE IN M/S)
WEATHER SUMMARY:
LOW ABOUT 990 NEAR FAROES IS MOV E. ANOTHER LOW 975 AT CAPE FAREWELL IS
MOV SLWY NE AND ASSOCIATED FRONTS IS SUNDAY MOV TOWARDS FAROES FM SW.
FCST FOR THE SEA-BANKS SURROUNDING THE FAROE ISLANDS - VALID 24 HRS:
OUTER-BANKS (YTRI):
SW 8 TO 13. SHWRS OTHERWISE GOOD VIS. DURING THE NIGHT RAIN FM SW WITH
MOD TO GOOD VIS. SUNDAY AFTERNOON IMPR VIS APART FM A FEW SHWRS.
MUNK-GROUND:
SW 10 TO 15 DECR AND SUNDAY 5 TO 10. DURING THE AFTERNOON INCR 8 TO 13.
SHWRS OTHERWISE GOOD VIS. SUNDAY RAIN FM SW WITH MOD TO GOOD VIS DURING
THE EVENING IMPR VIS.
FUGLOY-BANK:
IN N-ERN PART E 13 TO 18 DECR AND SUNDAY 8 TO 13 BECMG SE. SNOW LATER
BECMG SLEET AND RAIN AND MOD TO POOR VIS. OTHERWISE SW AND W 8 TO 13. SUNDAY
DECR 3 TO 8. SHWRS OTHERWISE GOOD VIS. SUNDAY AFTERNOON IN THE WHOLE WATER
SE AND S 5 TO 13 AND RAIN FM SW WITH MOD TO GOOD VIS. DURING THE EVENING
BECMG S AND SW 8 TO 13 AND IMPR VIS.
ICELAND RIDGE:
IN N-ERN PART E 13 TO 18 SLWY DECR 8 TO 13. SNOW LATER BECMG SLEET OR
RAIN WITH MOD TO POOR VIS. OTHERWISE SW 8 TO 13 BECMG S 5 TO 10. SHWRS
OTHERWISE GOOD VIS. SUNDAY IN THE WHOLE WATER BETWEEN SW AND SE 5 TO 10.
RAIN FM SW MOD TO GOOD VIS. FM LATE IN THE AFTERNOON BETWEEN SE AND SW 8
TO 13. DURING THE EVENING SW LOC GALE 15. IMPR VIS APART FM SHWRS.
